article.headline: SIU-Edwardsville secures 78-59 win against Lindenwood
article.description: — Damarco Minor's 17 points helped SIU-Edwardsville defeat Lindenwood 78-59 on Thursday night.
article.story: SAINT CHARLES, Mo. -- — Damarco Minor's 17 points helped SIU-Edwardsville defeat Lindenwood 78-59 on Thursday night. Minor added six rebounds for the Cougars (11-8, 4-2 Ohio Valley Conference). Lamar Wright scored 15 points and added eight rebounds and three blocks. Ray'Sean Taylor shot 4 for 11, including 4 for 7 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. Keenon Cole led the Lions (7-11, 1-4) in scoring, finishing with 14 points, nine rebounds and two blocks. Jaylon McDaniel added 13 points for Lindenwood. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
